div.h1: Types of Publications on Lens V2
div.p: Lens V2 has four different kinds of publications. They differ slightly in their logic, but main categories are Posts (unique root content) and Referring publications (Comments/Quotes/Mirrors that refer to the original Posts or to each other).

div.h1: Types of Publication Modules on Lens V2
div.p:
All publications (except Mirrors) may have different types of modules:
- Reference Modules
- Action Modules
- Collect Modules (*only V1)

div.span:
Reference Modules are called when a reference publication is created on a post that has a ReferenceModule.
Reference module can allow/disallow referring to the content (i.e. comments only from followers) and also make any other transactions (like pay-to-comment), monetary or not.
Only one Reference Module allowed per publication

div.style: display: flex; align-items: unsafe flex-start; justify-content: unsafe flex-start; width: 148px; height: 1px; padding-top: 587px; margin-left: 482px;
box-sizing: border-box; font-size: 0px; text-align: left;
display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; pointer-events: all; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: normal;
div.span:
Action Module makes it possible to perform any on-chain action on a given publication (donate, mint NFTs, Collect, Vote on Poll, etc).
It is a voluntary action that any Profile can perform by "acting" on a publication.
Publication can have several Action Modules enabled on it.

div.style: display: flex; align-items: unsafe flex-start; justify-content: unsafe flex-start; width: 148px; height: 1px; padding-top: 587px; margin-left: 642px;

display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Helvetica; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 1.2; pointer-events: all; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: normal;
div.span:
Legacy from Lens V1, similar to Action Module - but it only allows Collecting of a publication (by minting a copy of a publication as an NFT Collect).
These are left in protocol for compatibility with Lens V1 publications that already had this enabled. But you cannot set Legacy Collect Modules for Lens V2 posts.

ModuleGlobals contract tracks the whitelisting and unwhitelisting of Publication Modules and other things.
It is controlled by ModuleGovernance MultiSig.
At the current time, only Whitelisted modules are allowed to be enabled on Publications.
